      ],
      "modelAnswer": "ethers.js is smaller (~120KB vs ~590KB), has native TypeScript support, and separates Providers (read) from Signers (write). It offers human-readable ABI format. web3.js was the original library with a larger API surface. ethers.js is MIT licensed while web3.js uses LGPL. Both are actively maintained, but ethers.js is preferred for new projects."
